---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const description =
  'Terms and disclaimer for KenAshe.ai: informational content only, not professional advice, and how external links and intellectual property are handled.';
const updated = 'June 25, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms"
  description={description}
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Home', path: '/' },
    { name: 'Terms', path: '/terms/' },
  ]}
>
  <article class="legal">
    <header class="legal-header">
      <p class="page-mark" aria-hidden="true">// terms</p>
      <h1>Terms &amp; Disclaimer</h1>
      <p class="updated">Last updated {updated}</p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>Plain and short. By using this site, you agree to the following.</p>

      <h2>Informational only</h2>
      <p>
        Everything here is for general information and education. It is not professional advice,
        including accounting, tax, financial, legal, or investment advice, and it does not create
        any client or advisory relationship. I am a CPA by background, but nothing on this site is
        accounting or tax advice. For decisions that matter, talk to a qualified professional about
        your specific situation.
      </p>

      <h2>No guarantees</h2>
      <p>
        I write about tools, builds, and workflows that worked for me. AI and the tools around it
        change quickly, and your results may differ. Nothing here is a promise of any particular
        outcome.
      </p>

      <h2>External links</h2>
      <p>
        I link to third-party sites and tools for convenience. Those links are not endorsements,
        and I am not responsible for the content, accuracy, or practices of sites I do not control.
      </p>

      <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>
        The writing, design, and original material on this site are mine unless noted otherwise.
        You are welcome to quote or reference it with credit and a link. Please do not republish
        whole pieces without permission. Any code samples are provided for you to learn from and
        use at your own risk.
      </p>

      <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>
        Please do not misuse the site, attempt to disrupt it, or scrape it in ways that degrade it
        for others.
      </p>

      <h2>As is</h2>
      <p>
        The site is provided "as is," without warranties of any kind. To the extent allowed by
        law, I am not liable for any loss or damage arising from your use of it.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        I may update these terms from time to time. The "last updated" date above reflects the
        current version.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions: <a href="mailto:hello@kenashe.ai">hello@kenashe.ai</a>. This page is a
        lightweight summary, not legal advice.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal {
    max-width: 44rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 4rem 1.5rem 0;
  }
  .legal-header {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }
  .page-mark {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .legal-header h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 3.5rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.035em;
    line-height: 1;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    color: var(--fg);
  }
  .updated {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
